import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Load US states shapefile
    us_states = gpd.read_file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json")
    
    # Group data by state and count cities
    state_counts = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='city_count')
    
    # Merge state_counts with us_states geodataframe
    merged_data = us_states.set_index('name').join(state_counts.set_index('state'))
    
    # Plot choropleth map
    merged_data.plot(column='city_count', cmap='coolwarm', linewidth=0.8, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of cities across states?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='first_letter', data=data, order=data['first_letter'].value_counts().index)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of cities based on their first letter?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['count'] = 1
    grouped_data = data.groupby(['state', 'first_letter']).count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='count', hue='first_letter', data=grouped_data, ci=None)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities in each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
